<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="231" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,613,926]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,829,854]" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described based on a single male. While it is currently placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[1228,1346,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Ptilothyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1228,1346,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="231">Ptilothyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, genital examination of this specimen is needed to clearly define its generic position.
</paragraph>
